From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Hermes Agent <hermes@nousresearch.com>
Date: Thu, 12 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: ARM: dts: sun8i-h3: Replace NanoPi-NEO board dts with FriendlyElec
 version

Replace the board-level device tree for NanoPi-NEO with the FriendlyElec
version. The board dts is kept minimal (just include the common dtsi +
enable EMAC with MII PHY), since all peripherals (USB, UART, I2C, SPI,
HDMI, audio, LEDs, etc.) are configured in the shared dtsi.

Changes vs upstream:
- Model: "FriendlyElec NanoPi-NEO" (was "FriendlyARM NanoPi NEO")
- Compatible: friendlyelec,nanopi-neo (was friendlyarm,nanopi-neo)
- Removed board-level ehci0/ohci0/usb_otg/usbphy — these are now in dtsi
- Removed board-level aliases — these are now in dtsi
- Kept only EMAC with MII PHY and allwinner,leds-active-low

